reviewText: I'm really not sure if the acting was actually that bad or if it was mostly a bad script. The photography was, at times, brilliant, although the print wasn't, tending towards muddy. There may well be folks out there who will find this film, for all it's flaws, interesting. I only managed to last 10 or 15 minutes. I'm getting old and don't want to waste any of what time I have left watching this drivel.
